Data Sampling: - Download validation dataset: cernbox.cern.ch/Upgrade_Data_v4 - Size: 78TB (compressed root files) - Checksum verification mandatory 2. Analysis Procedures:  Tracking: Validate with Phase-1 alignment constants (attached)  Muon ID: Apply updated selection criteria: cms.cern/muon-selection-2024  Jets: Use new JEC files: cms.cern/JEC_Fall2024 3. Submission Requirements: - Comparative histograms for standard track reconstruction - RunTheMatrix test results with status flags - Computing resource log (CPU/GPU hours) Resource Allocation:  Priority grid access: CMS Tier-2 sites reserved until Oct 30  GPU farm scheduling: submit-gpu.cern.ch (use queue "upgrade-verif")  Storage quotas increased by 200TB for verification datasets Consequences of Inaction: - Physics publication moratorium on Run 4 data until resolution - Potential 3-month delay in top quark coupling analysis - Compromise to dark matter search sensitivity goals Required Actions By Oct 10: 1. Dataset verification acknowledgement: cms-logbook.cern.ch/entry?type=verification 2. Assign institutional contact: portal.cms.cern/upgrade-contacts 3. Submit preliminary report: cms.cern/verification-report-form The credibility of high-energy physics depends on our vigilance. Execute with urgency.
